			<Body>
				<Text Type="text">
					&lt;p&gt;In a Half and Half (also known as a "Black and Tan" in certain locations), the primary factor will be the density of the two beers -- one beer &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_and_Tan#Preparation"&gt;must be of a lesser density&lt;/a&gt; than the other to stay afloat.  Contrasting colors are used for visual effect; otherwise, how might you know one was floating?&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p&gt;Common recipes involve floating the less dense Guinness over a Bass, or a Guinness over a Harp Lager.  Its Guinness' particular light density that makes it a good candidate for so many half-and-half style recipes.&lt;/p&gt;

				</Text>
			</Body>
		</Instance>
